Durban - A man believed to be a rank manager was shot and killed while seated in his car outside Chester Meats on Inwabi Road in Isipingo Rail this morning. Alpha Alarms who were first on the scene together with Metro Police and Isipingo SAPS said the driver and passenger were seated in the vehicle, when they were allegedly approached by three men on foot who fired shots and fled. “One person, believed to be a passenger in a van was shot dead whilst the driver, alleged to be a rank manager, was also shot, and was rushed to hospital in a critical condition,” posted Alpha Alarms on Facebook. The security company said no description of the suspects could be obtained and the suspects fled on foot into the busy surroundings. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane confirmed that the shooting that took place today at 8:00 on Inwabi Road in Isipingo. “It is alleged that two males were shot by three suspects, one was confirmed dead at the scene while the other victim was taken to hospital for medical attention. It is unknown what caused the shooting,” said Zwane. The Mercury